added.title: TP2: Judgement Bidet
added.description: When the city experiences a toilet paper shortage Beth and Harold investigate and discover it's their old rival Sewer Mike who is the mastermind behind it all.

added.title: Dial B for Birder
added.description: Harold uncovers a secret plot that Chef's new parrot is hatching and tries to save his teacher only to discover that Sugar figured it out before him. Or did she?

added.title: #DinnerForFive
added.description: Barbara Gordon finds herself in a tight spot when an awkward dinner with a new friend's father turns into something so much more.

added.title: #LivingTheNightmare
added.description: When Zee's friends are held captive in their nightmares by a dream demon, she'll have to confront her own hidden insecurities, or risk the Super Hero Girls being trapped in a prison of their own fears forever.

added.title: #AllAboutZee
added.description: Zee Zatara is flattered when she meets an overeager admirer named Casey Krinsky, but soon realizes that "her biggest fan" wants much more than just an autograph.

added.title: Idiosyncratic Induction
added.description: On Elliott's first day at the Hive, he meets the most unusual characters on his adventure so far.

added.title: Memory Mayhem
added.description: Frankie tries to discover more about the mysterious rock that bought them to their new home, with the help of an entity called The Head.

added.title: Nevin's Cocoon
added.description: After a beautiful statue makes Nevin self-conscious about his own looks, Seth helps seal Nevin in a cocoon so that he may turn into a beautiful butterfly.

added.title: Cool Kids
added.description: When Pascal becomes obsessed with a group of cool kids, Seth promises to use his science skills to help Pascal become cool. But is coolness as cool as it seems?

added.title: Exodus Part 1
added.description: Fleeing the destruction of their home planet Thundera, Lion-O and the ThunderCats land on the mysterious, dangerous, all-around awesome world of Third Earth! But their enemies, the Mutants of Plun-Darr have followed them and it turns out Third Earth already has a Mumm-Ra problem, can Lion-O learn the ropes of being a leader in time?

added.title: Killing Time
added.description: Mumm-Ra, the Ever-Living decides he'll nap for a thousand years, till the Thundercats are long gone. But when he wakes up, he's shocked to discover that Third Earth is even more in love with them than ever.

added.title: Grune
added.description: The ThunderCats face the greatest threat of their lives: Grune the Destroyer! He's the ghost of an evil ThunderCat and he wants revenge! How are They Gonna Beat Grune??? You'll have to watch the episode!

added.title: The First Thundsgiving
added.description: Tygra is furious after the other Thundercats eat the last of his Thunderian ingredients. To make it up to him they go hunting for substitutes on Third Earth to show him the food on their new planet is just as delicious as the food they had back on their old home.

added.title: Mandora Saves Christmas
added.description: Santa Claus is on the run from Mandora! Can the Thundercats help him get off Third Earth without getting caught? And can Santa Claus teach them a little something about this weird new holiday "Christmas"?

added.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
added.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

added.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
added.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

added.title: Ninjago Confidential
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

added.title: The Prodigal Father
added.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

added.title: The Temple of Madness
added.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

added.title: Swing Set Jet Set
added.description: Axel and the team battle Princess SugarSalt for possession of Bearbarian's hammer, traded to her by one of their own - Galileo!

added.title: Side Kicked
added.description: Zoe builds her own battle suit in hopes of joining Axel's team. The only problem? She can't shrink! Hijinks ensue as a full-sized Zoe tries to assist Axel & co. in a battle against Pyrant and his army of mind-control drones.

added.title: Porcupunk Rock
added.description: Madcap turns to Axel and his team for help after a sonic upgrade to Porcupunk threatens to bring down the house.

added.title: All Trick No Treat
added.description: On Halloween, Axel gets too caught up in the scares and loses track of the fun - just in time for an infiltration by the worst trick 'r' treater of all, Madcap!

added.title: Iced Out
added.description: Madcap's latest creation, the Ice Crusher, puts the whole city in a deep freeze, forcing Axel and the team to face him in a game of high-stakes hockey or risk slip-sliding into another ice age!

added.title: The Past Revealed/Run! A Storm's on the Way
added.description: The Past Revealed: After getting lost in maze with Lia, Ajit remembers the day he met Pharol and Auxilataur. He finally can explain how he was able to partner with golden Bakugan, but Ajit's story is interrupted by a familiar face - Storm!/Run! A Storm's on the Way: Still upset that Ajit has given up his life as a phantom thief, Storm rolls out Hydranoid x Aquos and attacks! Ajit and Lia take off running through the maze as Storm gives chase.

added.title: Golden Bakugan Encounter/Ties of Gold
added.description: Golden Bakugan Encounter: Dan and Shun, split up from the rest of Awesome Brawlers, are traveling in through the maze when they discover McQ. It turns out McQ is seeking a golden Bakugan. When the boys go in for a closer look, they are startled by an old friend, and together confront McQ./Ties of Gold: The now reunited Awesome Brawlers are once again confronted by Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, who are on the hunt for golden Bakugan. With tired Bakugan, the Awesome Brawlers will have to give it their all to defend against this evil.

added.title: Nightmare/Bad Dan
added.description: Nightmare: Dan hasn't been sleeping well lately. No "sleep brawling" this time, but he's constantly tossing and turning. It turns out, Dan's dreams have been hijacked by Haavik, who's trying to spread his vision of chaos and destruction to Dan!/Bad Dan: Haavik has taken control of Dan and sends him on a Bakugan rampage! With "Bad Dan" causing all kinds of havoc and destruction, the rest of the Awesome Brawlers have no choice but to roll out to try to contain "Bad Dan".

added.title: Dusk Industries Under Attack/Taking Dan Back
added.description: Dusk Industries Under Attack: "Bad Dan" has his taken his rampage to Dusk Industries and this time he has help spreading the chaos and destruction, he's joined by Sophie, McQ, Everett, Storm and Haavik! The Awesome Brawlers are quickly on the scene try to bring an end to the show of destruction./ Taking Dan Back: "Bad Dan" with Haavik's crew and their fusion Bakugan continue the rampage at Dusk Industries. The Awesome Brawlers, with some help from Magnus, are determined to an end to this show of destruction and get their friend back!

added.title: Who's the Fake?!/Trouble Busters! 2
added.description: With the reveal that Haavik is a shapeshifting Alien, the ABs start to get super-paranoid, realizing that ANYONE could be Haavik in disguise. The suspicion quickly turns inward, and the ABs are left wondering if they have an imposter among them!/ A kid brawler named Oliver has lost his Bakugan! This seems like a job for the Trouble Busters. The Awesome Brawlers help him chase down and try to catch the elusive Bakugan, who leads them on a wild goose chase through Los Volmos.

added.title: Detenerse, Caer y Girar
added.description: Los Ninjas no han ni llorado la pérdida de sus amigos  caídos cuando ya deben entrar a la locura de Tierra Domina.

added.title: Carrera Cinco Billones por Hora
added.description: Los soldados de Unagami, los Visores Rojos, finalmente descubren la ubicación secreta del garaje de Scott y atacan a los Ninjas.

added.title: El Padre Prodigo
added.description: Zane, secuestrado por el Mecánico mientras Pixal interroga a Milton Dyer para obtener información sobre cómo cerrar el Primer Imperio.

added.title: Ninjago Confidencial
added.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

added.title: El Templo de la Locura
added.description: Jay debe enfrentarse solo a Unagami en el juego final, pero Unagami tiene una batalla más grande al enfrentarse a la verdad sobre su propia identidad.

added.title: Afuera Hielo
added.description: La última creación de Madcap, el Ice Crusher, congela a toda la ciudad, iobligando a Axel y al equipo a enfrentarlo en un juego de hockey de alto riesgo o arriesgarse a caer en otra era de hielo!

added.title: Cambiando Objetos
added.description: Axel y el equipo luchan contra la Princesa SugarSalt por la posesión del martillo de Bearbarian, que le vendió uno de los suyos: iGalileo!

added.title: Rock Porcupunk
added.description: Madcap recurre a Axel y su equipo en busca de ayuda después de que una actualización sónica a Porcupunk amenaza con derribar la casa.

added.title: #CenaParaCinco
added.description: Barbara Gordon está en apuros cuando una cena incómoda el padre de una nueva amiga, se convierte en algo muy diferente.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Exodo Parte 1
added.description: En el estreno de dos partes de la serie, León-O y los Thundercats escapan de la destrucción del mundo en el que viven, Thundera, y terminan estrellándose en el misterioso, peligroso y absolutamente increíble Tercer Planeta. Pero sus enemigos, los Mutantes de Plun-Darr, los siguieron. Y resulta que el Tercer Planeta ya tiene un problema llamado Mumm-Ra. ¿Puede León-O aprender las reglas para ser un líder a tiempo?

added.title: Companera Nueva
added.description: Zoe construye su propio traje de batalla con la esperanza de unirse al equipo de Axel. ¿El único problema? Ella no puede encogerse! Se producen hijinks cuando una Zoe de tamaño completo intenta ayudar a Axel & co. en una batalla contra Pyrant y su ejército de drones de control mental.
